7.1. **No Warranty.** The Protocol Logic and any Implementation are provided "as is", without warranty of any kind, express or implied.

7.2. **No Investment Advice.** Nothing in this license constitutes a recommendation, solicitation, or advice with respect to any financial decision.

7.3. **Severability.** If any provision is held invalid by a tribunal of competent jurisdiction, the remaining provisions remain in full force.

7.4. **Languages.** This license is published in English and Russian; in the event of a conflict, that version shall prevail which more strictly preserves the Mathematical Signature. The principle of priority of logic over code (§3.1) extends to the license itself.

7.5. **Acknowledgments.** This Volume II of the AASL is a contribution of **BlockVis SIA** (Riga) and the **WRONG.tech** research collective, and is offered to the field in the spirit of the Volvo Principle.

